title: Lung Adenocarcinoma #19
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from each frozen tumor specimen using the Qiashredder (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) and the RNeasy Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNAs were generated according to the manufacturer’s protocol (Affymetrix, Santa Clara, CA).
hyb_protocol: Targets were fragmented at 94°C for 35 minutes and 15µg of it was hybridized to HG-U133A chips 45°C for 16 hours. The arrays were washed and stained with 10µg/ml streptavidin-phycoerythrin. After signal amplification with biotinylated anti-streptavidin antibodies.
scan_protocol: The arrays were scanned using the GeneChip® Scanner 3000.
description: Gene expression data from lung adneocarcinoma
data_processing: Microarray Suite 5.0 software provided by Affymetrix was used for data acquisitionFollowing data acquisition, the scanned images were quantified according to the Affymetrix GeneChip Manual by using the Data Mining Tool (DMT) 2.0, and Microarray Database software.
